 closer to echinoderms than to vertebrates or tunicates.  Bourlat et al. (2006) tested this unusual hypothesis for systematic error by 1) adding more taxa, thereby enabling better detection of misleading multiple substitutions at the same site, and 2) removing problematic taxa with high rate of substitutions (and therefore susceptible to long branch attraction); in both tests, a monophyletic Chordata was inferred.  In a later paper, Delsuc et al. (2008) reanalyzed their data using an improved model of sequence evolution and using more genes and more taxa, and they inferred a monophyletic Chordata with good statistical support.',1,'ICZN','E. Haeckel ','node-based_standard','The most inclusive crown clade containing Petromyzon marinus Linnaeus 1758 but not Strongylocentrotus purpuratus Stimpson 1857. This is a branch-modified node based definition. Abbreviated definition: >Ã¢Ë†â€¡ Petromyzon marinus Linnaeus 1758 ~ Strongylocentrotus purpuratus Stimpson 1857','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \ndescription: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: \"\"\n    title: \"\"\n    publisher: \"\"\n    book_editors: \"\"\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"\"\n    edition: \"\"\n    city: \"\"\n    volume: \"\"\n    pages: \"\"\n    keywords: \"\"\n    abstract: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: book\npreexisting: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Haeckel, E.\n    title: Anthropogenie oder Entwickelungsgeschichte des Menschen\n    publisher: \"\"\n    book_editors: \"\"\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"1874\"\n    edition: \"\"\n    city: Engelmann, Leipzig\n    volume: \"\"\n    pages: \"22\"\n    keywords: \"\"\n    abstract: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: b