y existed for this taxon, so the name Urochordata was not needed. The name Tunicata is almost universally used to refer to this group of organisms in the major monographic works, including Alder (1863), Van Name (1945), Berrill (1950) and Bone (1998) and it is more frequently used.  It was selected for the clade named here for those reasons.',1,'ICZN','J. B. Lamarck ','node-based_crown_clade_apomorphy-modified','The most inclusive crown clade exhibiting a tunic synapomorphic with that in Ciona intestinalis Linnaeus 1767.  The tunic is a covering that surrounds the mantle and organs of the animal and is composed of cellulose and protein.  This is an apomorphy-modified node-based definition.  Abbreviated definition: >âˆ‡ tunic (Ciona intestinalis Linnaeus  1767). ','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \nphylogeny: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Stach, T., and J. M. Turbeville\n    journal: \"Mol. Phyl. Evol. \"\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"2002\"\n    volume: \"25\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: 408-428\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: journal\n    title: Phylogeny of Tunicata inferred from molecular and morphological characters.\n  \"1\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: \"Turon X. and S. L\\xC3\\xB3pez-Legentil\"\n    journal: Mol. Phylogenet. Evol.\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"2004\"\n    volume: \"33\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: 309-320\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: journal\n    title: \"Ascidian molecular phylogeny inferred from mtDNA data with emphasis on the Aplousobranchiata. \"\n  \"2\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Yokobori S., A. Kurabayashi, B. A. Neilan, T. Maruyama, and E. Hirose\n    journal: Mol. Ph