es (sensu Thorne and Reveal, 2007) because the former is much more frequently used. ',1,'ICBN','J. Lindley ','node-based_crown_clade_branch-modified','The least inclusive clade containing Gentiana lutea Linnaeus 1753 (Gentianaceae) and Cinchona pubescens Vahl 1790 (Rubiaceae).  This is a node-based definition in which both of the specifiers are extant; it is intended to apply to a crown clade.  Abbreviated definition: < Gentiana lutea Linnaeus 1753 & Cinchona pubescens Vahl 1790.  ','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \npreexisting: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Lindley, J.\n    title: Nixus plantarum.\n    publisher: Ridgway and Sons\n    book_editors: \"\"\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"1833\"\n    edition: \"\"\n    city: \" London\"\n    volume: \"\"\n    pages: \"\"\n    keywords: \"\"\n    abstract: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: book\nprimary-phylogeny: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Backlund, M., B. Oxelman, and B. Bremer\n    journal: Am. J. Bot.\n    figure: 1, 2\n    year: \"2000\"\n    volume: \"87\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: \"1029\\xE2\\x80\\x931043\"\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: journal\n    title: Phylogenetic relationships within the Gentianales based on ndhF and rbcL sequences, with particular reference to the Loganiaceae.\nphylogeny: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Olmstead, R. G., B. Bremer, K. M. Scott, and J. D. Palmer\n    journal: Ann. Mo. Bot. Gard.\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"1993\"\n    volume: \"80\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: \"700\\xE2\\x80\\x93722\"\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn