\nThe clade name Compsopogonophyceae is converted from Compsopogonophyceae Saunders & Hommersand 2004, a class name under the rank-based system, which they applied to the same clade to which it is applied here.  It was the only class in the subphylum Metarhodophytina Saunders & Hommersand 2004 (an elevation in rank of Magneâ€™s (1989) Metarhodophycidae). The name Compsopogonophyceae is the more widely used of the three names and is therefore selected here for conversion to a clade name.\n',1,'ICBN','G.W. Saunders & M.H. Hommersand ','node-based_crown_clade_branch-modified','The ost inclusive crown clade that contains Compsopogon caeruleus (C. Agardh) Montagne 1846 and Rhodochaete pulchella Thuret ex Bornet 1892 but not Bangia fuscopurpurea (Dillwyn) Lyngbye 1819, Porphyridium aerugineum Geitler 1923, Rhodella maculata L. Evans 1970 or Stylonema cornu-cervi Reinsch 1875. This definition is branch-modified node-based and designates a crown clade. The inclusion of a second internal specifier ensures that the name will not apply to any clade if Compsopogonales, Rhodochaetales, and Erythropeltidales do not form a clade. Abbreviated definition: >ïƒ‘ Compsopogon caeruleus (C. Agardh) Montagne 1846 & Rhodochaete pulchella Thuret ex Bornet 1892 ~ Bangia fuscopurpurea (Dillwyn) Lyngbye 1819 ïƒš Porphyridium aerugineum Geitler 1923 ïƒš Rhodella maculata L. Evans 1970 ïƒš Stylonema cornu-cervi Reinsch 1875.','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \npreexisting: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Saunders, G.W., and M.H. Hommersand\n    journal: Am. J. Bot.\n    title: Assessing red algal supraordinal diversity and taxonomy in the context of contemporary systematic data.\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"2004\"\n    volume: \"91\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: 1494-1507\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_typ