BN','L. Le Gall & G.W. Saunders','node-based_crown_clade_branch-modified','The clade originating with the most recent common ancestor of Corallina officinalis Linnaeus 1758 and Rhodogorgon ramosissima J.N. Norris & Bucher 1989. This definition is node-based and, as the specifiers are both extant, designates a crown clade. Abbreviated definition: < Corallina officinalis Linnaeus 1758 & Rhodogorgon ramosissima J.N. Norris & Bucher 1989.','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \npreexisting: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Le Gall, L., and G.W. Saunders\n    journal: Mol. Phylogenet. Evol.\n    title: \"A nuclear phylogeny of the Florideophyceae (Rhodophyta) inferred from combined EF2, small subunit and large subunit ribosomal DNA: establishing the new red algal subclass Corallinophycidae.\"\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"2007\"\n    volume: \"43\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: 1118-1130\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: journal\nprimary-phylogeny: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Le Gall, L., and G.W. Saunders\n    journal: Mol. Phylogenet. Evol.\n    title: \"A nuclear phylogeny of the Florideophyceae (Rhodophyta) inferred from combined EF2, small subunit and large subunit ribosomal DNA: establishing the new red algal subclass Corallinophycidae.\"\n    figure: \"4\"\n    year: \"2007\"\n    volume: \"43\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: 1118-1130\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: journal\ndescription: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess {}\n\nphylogeny: []\n\n','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n\"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithI