antage of terminating this seemingly never-ending taxonomic shuffle in the literature and of assigning this clade a single name. The name traditionally associated with the rank of order (Cyanidiales), which has been widely applied in contemporary research, is selected here for consistency with published literature on the group.\n',1,'ICBN','T. Christensen ','node-based_crown_clade_branch-modified','The most inclusive crown clade that contains Cyanidium caldarium (J. Tilden) Geitler 1933 but not Compsopogon caeruleus (C. Agardh) Montagne 1846. This definition is branch-modified node-based and designates a crown clade. Abbreviated definition: >ïƒ‘ Cyanidium caldarium (J. Tilden) Geitler 1933 ~ Compsopogon caeruleus (C. Agardh) Montagne 1846.','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \nprimary-phylogeny: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: \"Yoon, H.S., K.M. M\\xC3\\xBCller, R.G. Sheath, F.D. Ott, and D. Bhattacharya\"\n    journal: J. Phycol.\n    title: Defining the major lineages of red algae (Rhodophyta).\n    figure: \"1\"\n    year: \"2006\"\n    volume: \"42\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: 482-492\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: journal\ndescription: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_type: book\n    citation_authors: \" \"\n    title: \" \"\npreexisting: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Christensen, T.\n    title: Alger.\n    publisher: \"\"\n    book_editors: \"T.W. B\\xC3\\xB6cher, M. Lange, and T. S\\xC3\\xB8rensen (Redig.)\"\n    series_editors: \"\"\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"1962\"\n    edition: \"\"\n    volumes: \"\"\n    city: \"\"\n    volume: \"\"\n    pages: \"1-178 \"\n    keywords: \"\"\n  