e (1989) was the base name for the subphylum name Eurhodophytina Saunders and Hommersand (2004). The latter is nonetheless better known in the literature and is selected here as the source for the converted clade name, rendering the former an approximate synonym under the PhyloCode. Macrorhodophytina Cavalier-Smith (1998) was a subphylum erected to contain all of Eurhodophytina as defined here, but also species of Rhodochaetales, thus the name referred to a group that we now consider to be polyphyletic. Saunders and Hommersand (2004) rejected Cavalier-Smithâ€™s construct as â€˜too broad to be appliedâ€™ to any of the groups they recognized and instead applied the name Eurhodophytina to the same clade to which it is applied here.\n',1,'ICBN','G.W. Saunders & M.H. Hommersand ','node-based_crown_clade_branch-modified','The clade originating with the most recent common ancestor of Bangia fuscopurpurea (Dillwyn) Lyngbye 1819 and Palmaria palmata (Linnaeus) Kuntze 1891. This definition is node-based and designates a crown clade. Abbreviated definition: < Bangia fuscopurpurea (Dillwyn) Lyngbye 1819 & Palmaria palmata (Linnaeus) Kuntze 1891.','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \nprimary-phylogeny: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: \"Yoon, H.S., K.M. M\\xC3\\xBCller, R.G. Sheath, F.D. Ott, and D. Bhattacharya\"\n    journal: J. Phycol.\n    title: Defining the major lineages of red algae (Rhodophyta).\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"2006\"\n    volume: \"42\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: 482-492\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: journal\ndescription: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_type: book\n    citation_authors: \" \"\n    title: \" \"\npreexisting: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0