ies with highly variable vegetative and reproductive attributes and life history strategies (Saunders and Kraft, 1997). Additionally, most freshwater florideophyte red algae are included in this clade. The monophyly of Nemaliophycidae was first demonstrated in a molecular study by Saunders et al. (1995) and has subsequently been corroborated in several other studies, most recently in the comprehensive molecular investigations of Harper and Saunders (2001, 2002) and Le Gall and Saunders (2007). \nThe converted clade name Nemaliophycidae is here defined so that it corresponds in composition to Nemaliophycidae sensu Le Gall and Saunders (2007). In contrast, Nemaliophycidae sensu Saunders and Hommersand (2004) applied to a larger group, which also contained species that are included here within Corallinophycidae.\n',1,'ICBN','T. Christensen','node-based_crown_clade_branch-modified','The most inclusive crown clade that contains Nemalion lubricum Duby 1830 (=Nemalion helminthoides (Velley) Batters 1902) but not Ahnfeltia plicata (Hudson) Fries 1836 or Chondrus crispus Stackhouse 1797 or Corallina officinalis Linnaeus 1758 or Hildenbrandia rubra (Sommerfelt) Meneghini 1841. This definition is branch-modified node-based and designates a crown clade. Abbreviated definition: >âˆ‡ Nemalion lubricum Duby 1830 ~ Ahnfeltia plicata (Hudson) Fries 1836 V Chondrus crispus Stackhouse 1797 V Corallina officinalis Linnaeus 1758 V Hildenbrandia rubra (Sommerfelt) Meneghini 1841.','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \nphylogeny: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Harper, J.T., and G.W. Saunders\n    journal: J. Phycol.\n    title: Molecular systematics of the Florideophyceae (Rhodophyta) using nuclear large and small subunit rDNA sequence data.\n    figure: \"\"\n    year: \"2001\"\n    volume: \"37\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: 1073-1082\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    u