idiophyceae H.S. Yoon, K.M. MÃ¼ller, R.G. Sheath, F.D. Ott & D. Bhattacharya in the rank-based system; these authors applied the name to the same clade to which it is applied here.  The names Porphyridiales and Porphyridiaceae (see Synonyms) are much more widely used in the literature but have not been applied consistently to this clade, having wide and variable applications in various treatments over the decades.  In contrast, the name Porphyridiophyceae applies unambiguously to this clade.  Silva (1996, p. 913) provides critical insights into the nomenclature of this clade under the rank-based system.\n',1,'ICBN','H.S. Yoon, K.M. MÃ¼ller, R.G. Sheath, F.D. Ott & D. Bhattacharya','node-based_crown_clade_branch-modified','The most inclusive crown clade that contains Porphyridium cruentum (S.F. Gray) NÃ¤geli 1849 (= Porphyridium purpureum (Bory de Saint-Vincent) K.M. Drew & R. Ross 1965) but not Bangia fuscopurpurea (Dillwyn) Lyngbye 1819, Compsopogon caeruleus (C. Agardh) Montagne 1846, Rhodella maculata L. Evans 1970, Rhodochaete pulchella Thuret ex Bornet 1892 or Stylonema alsidii (Zanardini) K.M. Drew 1956. This definition is branch-modified node-based and designates a crown clade. Abbreviated definition: >âˆ‡ Porphyridium cruentum (S.F. Gray) NÃ¤geli 1849 ~ Bangia fuscopurpurea (Dillwyn) Lyngbye 1819 V Compsopogon caeruleus (C. Agardh) Montagne 1846 V Rhodella maculata L. Evans 1970 V Rhodochaete pulchella Thuret ex Bornet 1892 V Stylonema alsidii (Zanardini) K.M. Drew 1956. ','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \nphylogeny: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: \"M\\xC3\\xBCller K.M., M.C. Oliveira, R.G. Sheath, and D. Bhattacharya\"\n    journal: Am. J. Bot.\n    title: Ribosomal DNA phylogeny of the Bangiophycidae (Rhodophyta) and the origin of secondary plastids.\n    figure: \"1\"\n    year: \"\"\n    volume: \"88\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: 1390-1400