ampanuloideae, a node-based definition with three specifiers works well.\nThe name Campanulaceae was applied to this clade by Shetler and Morin (1986), Kolakowski (1994), and Takhtajan (1997).  However, following Wagenitz (1964) and Cronquist (1981), most authors have used the name Campanuloideae for this clade, applying the name Campanulaceae to a more inclusive clade. The latter application of these two names is adopted here.',1,'ICBN','Burnett','node-based_crown_clade_branch-modified','The clade originating with the most recent common ancestor of Campanula latifolia Linnaeus 1753, Wahlenbergia linifolia A. de Candolle 1830, and Platycodon grandiflorus (Jacquin) A. de Candolle 1830. This is a node-based definition in which all of the specifiers are extant and therefore designates a crown clade. Abbreviated definition: < Campanula latifolia Linnaeus 1753 & Wahlenbergia linifolia A. de Candolle 1830 & Platycodon grandiflorus (Jacquin) A. de Candolle 1830.','--- !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \nphylogeny: !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n  \"0\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: Eddie, W. M. M., T. Shulkina, J. Gaskin, R. C. Haberle, and R. K. Jansen\n    journal: Ann. Mo. Bot. Gard.\n    title: Phylogeny of Campanulaceae s. str. inferred from ITS Sequences of Nuclear Ribosomal DNA.\n    figure: \"1\"\n    year: \"2003\"\n    volume: \"90\"\n    number: \"\"\n    pages: 554-575\n    keywords: \"\"\n    isbn: \"\"\n    url: \"\"\n    doi: \"\"\n    treebase_tree_id: \"\"\n    citation_type: journal\n  \"1\": !map:ActiveSupport::HashWithIndifferentAccess \n    citation_authors: \" Haberle, R. C., A. Dang, T. Lee, C. Penaflor, H. Cortes-Burn, A. Oestreich, L. Raubenson, N. Cellinese, E. J. Edwards, S.-T. Kim, W. M. M. Eddie, and R. K. Jansen\"\n    journal: Taxon\n    title: Taxonomic and biogeographic implications of a phylogenetic analysis of the Campanulaceae based on three chloroplast genes.\n    fig